16/11/2003
ANKARA, Turkey -- Foreign Minister Abdullah Gul and Croatian European Integration Minister Neven Mimica met on Friday (14 November) to discuss stability and security in Southeast Europe. 
They agreed that closer co-operation would be mutually beneficial with regard to their countries' efforts to join the EU. 
Mimica also met with Turkish Secretary-General for EU Integration Murat Sungar to discuss political, economic and commercial co-operation opportunities. 
Trade volume between Turkey and Croatia has increased by 90 per cent since a free trade agreement was signed earlier this year.
In other news, Turkish personnel captured more than 200 illegal immigrants in two separate operations Saturday. 
Most were from Iraq, Bangladesh and Pakistan. 
(Anadolu Agency - 15/11/03; Anadolu Agency, HINA - 14/11/03)
